## 12. Accessibility for Non-Academic Users
Open science is for everyone—citizen scientists, industry professionals, policymakers, and hobbyists. Start with:
- **Citizen Science**: Contribute observations via [iNaturalist](https://www.inaturalist.org/) (e.g., upload nature photos).
- **Data Sharing**: Upload files to [Zenodo](https://zenodo.org/) without a DOI for personal projects.
- **Analysis**: Use [Jupyter Notebooks](https://jupyter.org/try-jupyter) for free, interactive coding.
- **Community Engagement**: Join [Zooniverse](https://www.zooniverse.org/) for citizen science projects.
All tools are explained in plain language, with tutorials linked for ease of use.

