## 13. Practical Workflow & Visualization

### Research Lifecycle Flow
The following steps guide researchers through open science practices. See the interactive flowchart below for a visual overview.

**STEP 1: PLAN & PRE-REGISTER**  
- Tools: [OSF Registries](https://osf.io/registries/), [Protocols.io](https://www.protocols.io/), [DMPTool](https://dmptool.org/)  
- *Example*: Pre-register on OSF: Create an account, select a template, document your hypothesis, and submit for a timestamped record.

**STEP 2: COLLECT DATA**  
- Tools: [Zenodo](https://zenodo.org/), [Dryad](https://datadryad.org/), [Dataverse](https://dataverse.org/), [REDCap](https://projectredcap.org/), [LabArchives](https://www.labarchives.com/)  
- *Example*: Publish on Zenodo: Log in, upload files, add metadata (title, authors, license), reserve a DOI, and publish.

**STEP 3: ANALYZE**  
- Tools: [Jupyter Notebooks](https://jupyter.org/try-jupyter), [GitHub](https://github.com/), reproducible code

**STEP 4: PUBLISH PREPRINT**  
- Tools: [arXiv](https://arxiv.org/), [bioRxiv](https://www.biorxiv.org/), domain-specific preprint servers

**STEP 5: PEER REVIEW**  
- Tools: [OpenReview](https://openreview.net/), traditional journals with open access options

**STEP 6: PRESERVE & ARCHIVE**  
- Tools: [Internet Archive](https://archive.org/), [Software Heritage](https://www.softwareheritage.org/), [CLOCKSS](https://clockss.org/), [Globus](https://www.globus.org/)

**STEP 7: TRACK IMPACT**  
- Tools: [Dimensions](https://www.dimensions.ai/), [Lens.org](https://www.lens.org/), [Altmetric](https://www.altmetric.com/)

**STEP 8: ENGAGE COMMUNITY**  
- Tools: [Zooniverse](https://www.zooniverse.org/), [iNaturalist](https://www.inaturalist.org/), social media

**Throughout all steps**: Apply [FAIR Principles](https://www.go-fair.org/fair-principles/), [CARE Ethics](https://www.gida-global.org/care), [ORCID](https://orcid.org/), [CRediT](https://credit.niso.org/)

